replies.body:
Allow me to help:

Morg, waveclear and save your Q to when he tries to engage on you, use shield on his nado, if he ults you you ult him, your ult range is large enough to keep him there even if he has minions to dash (also your ult slow hurts his dash speed, making it even more difficult to escape);

Zed: play safe the first two lvls, use your Q to farm and to poke him, save your ult to dodge his nado since he needs to hit it to ult you, be careful to avoid having his WW block your Q, especially if you are all-ining;

Talon: Skill match-up, both have strong lvl2 so most of the times depends on who wins the 1v1 here, I recommend you use your W once to remove his shield, and all-in him when his shields down, or if he tries to play aggressive, auto him and then use your melee Q in him;

Veigar: There isn't much you can do in this match-up really, play safe and stack, be careful to not get hit by his nado if he is inside your cage, because he can ult you without getting stunned (his ult is a blink, therefore is not stopped by your E), and then you won't have CC to stop him. The only way you are going to kill him is if he gets misplays and gets stunned, then he should be easy to kill. (I recommend putting a few points in E, to increase his stun duration, so you can combo him without the risk of him breaking free of the stun and using WW to block your ult.).

Also get armor yellows and exhaust on morg and veig(seeker's armguard aldo helps). Tabi's if you are losing with zed or talon.
